snippet: Off-spinner Nathan Lyon captured three wickets as Pakistan slumped to 91 for five on the fifth afternoon of the second test on Friday, a collapse that put Australia on target for a series-clinching victory....
lead_paragraph: Off-spinner Nathan Lyon captured three wickets as Pakistan slumped to 91 for five on the fifth afternoon of the second test on Friday, a collapse that put Australia on target for a series-clinching victory.

headline.main: Lyon Haul Leaves Australia Scenting Victory
